02:17.517 --> 02:19.586
♪♪♪♪

02:19.586 --> 02:21.421
OH, WHERE THE HELL...
YOU ALL RIGHT?

02:21.421 --> 02:23.023
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

02:23.023 --> 02:25.425
STAY AWAY FROM ME.

02:25.425 --> 02:26.793
WHERE ARE THEY?

02:26.793 --> 02:28.729
CAN I HELP YOU AT ALL?
I SAID, "STAY AWAY FROM ME"!

02:28.729 --> 02:30.430
OKAY, OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT.

02:30.430 --> 02:32.298
WHERE THE HELL ARE MY KEYS?

02:34.735 --> 02:36.803
WHERE THE HELL...

02:36.803 --> 02:38.939
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

02:41.542 --> 02:43.376
CAN I TALK TO YOU?

02:43.376 --> 02:46.580
YOU HAVE
NOTHING TO SAY TO ME.

02:46.580 --> 02:48.148
YOU NEED TO TALK
TO ME, DAVID.

02:48.148 --> 02:51.017
I SAID, "YOU HAVE
NOTHING TO SAY TO ME."

02:51.017 --> 02:53.554
YOU NEED TO HEAR ME OUT.

02:56.857 --> 02:59.225
HERE.

02:59.225 --> 03:01.835
GIVE ME THE KEY.

03:01.835 --> 03:05.005
LISTEN TO ME, DAVID.

03:05.005 --> 03:07.440
I'M LISTENING.

03:07.440 --> 03:09.643
THEN LET IT GO.

03:09.643 --> 03:12.245
TURN OUR PHONES
BACK ON RIGHT NOW.

03:12.245 --> 03:14.447
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU DID TO THEM,

03:14.447 --> 03:16.449
BUT YOU NEED
TO MAKE IT STOP,

03:16.449 --> 03:19.052
'CAUSE YOU'RE HEADING UP
THE WRONG ROAD, MY MAN.

03:19.052 --> 03:21.755
THE WRONG ROAD.

03:21.755 --> 03:25.325
NOW, YOU HEAR
WHAT I'M SAYING.

03:25.325 --> 03:29.663
YOU AND THAT OTHER PUNK
HAD BETTER GET OUT OF THIS TOWN

03:29.663 --> 03:31.998
AND NOT LOOK BACK...

03:31.998 --> 03:33.366
BECAUSE TOMORROW MORNING,

03:33.366 --> 03:36.069
I AM GOING TO BRING HELL
ON THIS PLACE

03:36.069 --> 03:38.739
THE LIKES OF WHICH
YOU HAVE NEVER SEEN.

03:38.739 --> 03:41.141
I WOULDN'T DO THAT
IF I WERE YOU.

03:41.141 --> 03:42.843
YOU'RE NOT ME.

03:42.843 --> 03:45.345
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

03:45.345 --> 03:47.614
YOUR PHONE'S RINGING.
MY PHONE IS IN MY CAR.

03:47.614 --> 03:49.950
YOUR PHONE IS RINGING
IN YOUR CAR.

03:49.950 --> 03:52.452
MY KEYS.

03:53.086 --> 03:55.088
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

03:55.088 --> 03:57.457
DUST BY THE MORNING.

03:57.457 --> 03:59.459
THAT PHONE CALL
MIGHT CHANGE YOUR MIND.

04:04.638 --> 04:06.773
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

04:11.845 --> 04:13.880
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

04:19.385 --> 04:20.554
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

04:20.554 --> 04:21.988
HELLO?

04:21.988 --> 04:24.390
ROSE: David.

04:24.390 --> 04:26.059
WHO IS THIS?

04:26.059 --> 04:28.529
Mama Rose.

04:28.529 --> 04:31.197
WHAT IS IT, ROSE?

04:31.197 --> 04:33.733
I know
you don't know that kid.

04:33.733 --> 04:37.203
Quite handsome, isn't he?

04:37.203 --> 04:39.405
WHO?
Him.

04:39.405 --> 04:41.241
The one in front of you.

04:44.010 --> 04:46.046
ARE YOU WATCHING ME?

04:46.046 --> 04:48.549
We're behind you.

04:58.124 --> 05:00.360
WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON?

05:00.360 --> 05:02.536
His name is Mitch.

05:02.536 --> 05:05.506
Do you know him?

05:05.506 --> 05:07.207
I KNOW HE WORKS HERE.

05:07.207 --> 05:08.775
You're not thinking.

05:08.775 --> 05:12.779
You know his last name.

05:12.779 --> 05:15.682
NO, ROSE, I DO NOT
KNOW HIS LAST NAME.

05:15.682 --> 05:18.752
Mitch Malone,
as in a Malone,

05:18.752 --> 05:22.856
as in my Malone,
as in my grandson.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.858
That's my grandson.

05:24.858 --> 05:26.159
You got it?

05:28.895 --> 05:30.230
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT, ROSE.

05:30.230 --> 05:32.065
Of course you didn't.

05:32.065 --> 05:34.234
He doesn't want
anybody to know that.

05:34.234 --> 05:35.802
He wants distance.

05:35.802 --> 05:37.738
He's only been working
the restaurant business,

05:37.738 --> 05:40.507
but he is Mitchell,
my grandson,

05:40.507 --> 05:43.043
and he wants nothing
to do with the business

05:43.043 --> 05:45.211
until he needs a favor.

05:45.211 --> 05:47.380
I HAD
NO WAY OF KNOWING THAT.

05:47.380 --> 05:50.483
I even tried to buy
that tow yard for him.

05:50.483 --> 05:53.954
He wouldn't take the money.

05:53.954 --> 05:57.023
He wants his own way.
You understand?

05:57.023 --> 06:02.268
So it's important to me
that he makes his own way.

06:02.268 --> 06:03.737
I UNDERSTAND.

06:03.737 --> 06:06.206
He's trying to walk
the straight and narrow.

06:06.206 --> 06:09.576
Get their phones back on
and leave them alone.

06:09.576 --> 06:11.512
I know this kid
is banging your wife,

06:11.512 --> 06:14.347
but leave them alone.

06:14.347 --> 06:16.850
Kid doesn't want
to be a gangster.

06:16.850 --> 06:18.151
I don't blame him.

06:18.151 --> 06:21.622
He wants to run a tow yard,
make his own way.

06:21.622 --> 06:23.990
So I need you
to let that happen.

06:23.990 --> 06:25.358
MAMA ROSE...

06:25.358 --> 06:28.161
David, I'm telling you
to let this go now.

06:28.161 --> 06:30.430
You know how it goes.

06:30.430 --> 06:33.934
D.'s here.
Let it go.

06:33.934 --> 06:35.669
OKAY.

06:35.669 --> 06:39.740
Get the phones back on ‐‐
now.

06:39.740 --> 06:40.774
OKAY.

06:40.774 --> 06:44.110
Thank you.

06:44.110 --> 06:45.546
OKAY.

06:45.546 --> 06:47.714
Have a good night.

06:47.714 --> 06:48.815
NIGHT, ROSE.

06:48.815 --> 06:50.517
[ LINE CLICKS ]

06:58.024 --> 06:59.259
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

06:59.259 --> 07:00.326
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

07:00.326 --> 07:02.603
Oscar.
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

07:02.603 --> 07:04.538
IT'S FINE.

07:04.538 --> 07:06.607
Good.

07:06.607 --> 07:10.010
HAVE THE PHONES TURNED
BACK ON AT BENNY'S TOW YARD.

07:10.010 --> 07:11.612
DAVID, ARE YOU SURE?

07:11.612 --> 07:13.614
DO IT NOW.

07:13.614 --> 07:15.816
ALL RIGHT,
GIVE ME TWO MINUTES.

07:15.816 --> 07:16.917
Thank you.

07:16.917 --> 07:19.052
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

07:22.188 --> 07:24.691
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

07:24.691 --> 07:26.860
YEAH, HI.
THIS IS BRANDON.

07:26.860 --> 07:29.896
I NEED THOSE PHONES
TURNED BACK ON RIGHT NOW.

07:29.896 --> 07:32.498
JUST DO IT.

07:32.498 --> 07:34.701
THANK YOU.
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

07:34.701 --> 07:36.537
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

08:18.384 --> 08:20.320
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

08:26.359 --> 08:27.728
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

08:29.295 --> 08:31.431
♪♪♪♪

08:35.468 --> 08:37.470
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

08:37.470 --> 08:39.840
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

08:39.840 --> 08:41.708
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

08:41.708 --> 08:42.976
HELLO?

08:42.976 --> 08:44.477
HI.

08:44.477 --> 08:46.112
Hi.

08:46.112 --> 08:47.447
WHERE ARE YOU?

08:47.447 --> 08:48.549
STILL HERE.

08:48.549 --> 08:50.684
Is he still there?

08:50.684 --> 08:53.386
YEP, HE HASN'T MOVED.

08:53.386 --> 08:55.889
WELL, I SHOULD HAVE
JUST STAYED THERE.

08:55.889 --> 08:57.390
WHY?

08:57.390 --> 08:58.825
GRAYSON CANCELED.

08:58.825 --> 09:01.702
[ SIGHS ]
THAT DUDE IS SUCH A FLAKE.

09:01.702 --> 09:03.336
I KNOW.

09:03.336 --> 09:05.639
HOW MUCH TIME
HAVE YOU PUT IN WITH HIM?

09:05.639 --> 09:08.509
TOO MUCH TIME
TO BACK AWAY NOW.

09:08.509 --> 09:10.110
SHALL I COME BACK?

09:10.110 --> 09:11.177
No.

09:11.177 --> 09:12.846
NO?

09:12.846 --> 09:17.250
NO, YOU SHOULD, UH, HEAD
TO THE SARANDON HOTEL BAR.

09:17.250 --> 09:18.885
WHY?

09:18.885 --> 09:22.823
By now is when David goes
to the bar trolling for drink.

09:22.823 --> 09:24.858
OH, YEAH?

09:24.858 --> 09:26.459
Yeah.

09:26.459 --> 09:28.662
OKAY.
SO, HOW SHOULD I MARK HIM?

09:28.662 --> 09:32.599
LET ME THINK.

09:32.599 --> 09:37.337
HIS WIFE IS, UH,
EVIL AND AGGRESSIVE.

09:37.337 --> 09:39.205
So he likes dominance.

09:39.205 --> 09:43.409
BUT HIS MISTRESS
WAS PASSIVE, BUT STRONG.

09:43.409 --> 09:45.078
So he likes passive.

09:45.078 --> 09:47.581
He's Southern, polite.

09:47.581 --> 09:51.618
LIKE A BAPTIST PREACHER,
HE LOVES A DAMSEL IN DISTRESS.

09:51.618 --> 09:54.287
SO BE A DAMSEL IN DISTRESS.

09:54.287 --> 09:56.857
Cry.

09:56.857 --> 09:58.892
Have a man make you cry.

09:58.892 --> 10:02.168
CALL LEE AND ASK HIM
IF HE CAN DO IT FOR YOU.

10:02.168 --> 10:03.837
OH, THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

10:03.837 --> 10:07.207
IF HE OFFERS YOU SOMETHING,
YOU GOT HIM.

10:07.207 --> 10:09.309
OKAY, SO, IF HE BUYS ME
A DRINK...

10:09.309 --> 10:11.344
He won't.
HE WON'T?

10:11.344 --> 10:12.478
NO, THAT'S TOO FORWARD.

10:12.478 --> 10:14.815
YOU HAVE TO UNDERSTAND ‐‐
HE...

10:14.815 --> 10:17.050
HE'S BEEN MARRIED
FOR A LONG TIME.

10:17.050 --> 10:18.819
HE'LL OFFER YOU
A HANDKERCHIEF,

10:18.819 --> 10:20.453
SO DON'T HAVE ONE.

10:20.453 --> 10:21.722
OR A TISSUE.

10:21.722 --> 10:25.191
Make sure there's none by
the bar, as well, so he can.

10:25.191 --> 10:29.930
LIKE I SAID, IF HE OFFERS
YOU SOMETHING, YOU GOT HIM.

10:29.930 --> 10:32.232
OKAY, I GOT IT.

10:32.232 --> 10:34.034
And be mean to him.

10:34.034 --> 10:35.435
[ CHUCKLES ] OKAY.

10:35.435 --> 10:38.171
DON'T ACCEPT
HIS INITIAL OFFER.

10:38.171 --> 10:39.773
THAT'S THE BAIT.

10:39.773 --> 10:42.175
You'll see him again.

10:42.175 --> 10:45.211
THAT'S HOW YOU HOOK HIM.

10:45.211 --> 10:47.013
I GOT IT.

10:47.013 --> 10:48.214
Good.

10:48.214 --> 10:50.751
GIRL, THIS IS
JUST LIKE OLD TIMES.

10:50.751 --> 10:53.119
YEAH, IT IS.

10:53.119 --> 10:54.988
BUT BIGGER FISH.
Yeah.

10:54.988 --> 10:56.990
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:56.990 --> 10:58.391
OKAY, I'M ON IT.

10:58.391 --> 11:02.368
AND FOR THE SECOND DATE,
WEAR SOMETHING YELLOW.

11:02.368 --> 11:03.904
WHY?

11:03.904 --> 11:05.906
HE LIKES SOUTHERN CHARM.

11:05.906 --> 11:09.943
[ Southern accent ] WELL,
SHOULD I HAVE A SOUTHERN ACCENT?

11:09.943 --> 11:10.977
DON'T DO THAT ACCENT.

11:10.977 --> 11:12.979
I'M JUST KIDDING.
[ Ringing ]

11:12.979 --> 11:15.448
THANK YOU.

11:15.448 --> 11:18.184
Who keeps calling you?

11:18.184 --> 11:19.385
NOBODY.

11:19.385 --> 11:21.522
OH, ALL RIGHT.

11:21.522 --> 11:23.423
WELL, I'LL LET YOU
KNOW HOW IT GOES.

11:23.423 --> 11:26.760
AND I'LL UPDATE YOU
ON THIS END.

11:26.760 --> 11:29.830
Bye.
BYE.

11:29.830 --> 11:31.397
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

11:35.769 --> 11:38.739
CHANGE OF PLANS ‐‐
SARANDON HOTEL.

11:44.110 --> 11:47.781
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

11:47.781 --> 11:50.216
WHY DO YOU KEEP CALLING ME?

11:50.216 --> 11:52.018
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

11:52.018 --> 11:53.186
[ SIGHS ]

11:53.186 --> 11:54.187
HELLO?

11:54.187 --> 11:55.188
HANNA: Candace?

11:55.188 --> 11:56.289
YES?

11:56.289 --> 11:57.958
I'M AT THE HOSPITAL.

11:57.958 --> 11:59.693
I HOPE IT'S SERIOUS.

11:59.693 --> 12:03.069
YOUR BABY IS STILL HERE.

12:06.072 --> 12:07.107
HELLO?

12:07.107 --> 12:09.042
I HEAR YOU.

12:09.042 --> 12:11.477
WHEN ARE YOU
COMING TO GET HIM?

12:13.714 --> 12:15.081
HELLO?

12:15.081 --> 12:18.251
H‐‐ HELLO?

12:18.251 --> 12:19.586
CANDACE, THEY ARE
REALLY GETTING READY

12:19.586 --> 12:21.021
to put him in foster care.

12:21.021 --> 12:22.789
Is that what you
really want?

12:23.857 --> 12:25.258
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

12:25.258 --> 12:27.160
HELLO?!

12:27.160 --> 12:30.063
HEL‐‐

12:30.063 --> 12:33.199
THIS DAMN GIRL DONE HUNG UP
THIS DAMN PHONE.

12:36.102 --> 12:37.403
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

12:37.403 --> 12:38.739
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

12:42.075 --> 12:44.477
CANDACE: <i>Hi. This is Candace.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

12:46.279 --> 12:47.981
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

12:47.981 --> 12:50.016
[ Ringing ]

12:50.016 --> 12:54.521
<i>Hi. This is Candace.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

12:54.521 --> 12:56.923
Mitch: COOL NOW?
THAT SON OF A BITCH!

12:56.923 --> 12:59.292
LOOKIT, MAN, IT'S ALL RIGHT.
NO, IT'S NOT ALL RIGHT.

12:59.292 --> 13:00.527
HE'S NOT TURNING
THE PHONES BACK ON.

13:00.527 --> 13:01.768
WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT HE DID TO THEM.

13:01.768 --> 13:03.403
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT.
THEY'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

13:03.403 --> 13:05.138
THEY'LL BE BACK ON, ALL RIGHT?
HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

13:05.138 --> 13:07.007
I TALKED TO HIM.
OH, YOU TALKED TO HIM.

13:07.007 --> 13:08.074
WHO THE HELL YOU THINK YOU ARE?

13:08.074 --> 13:09.209
DON'T QUESTION ME,
ALL RIGHT?

13:09.209 --> 13:10.644
I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.

13:10.644 --> 13:12.478
MITCH, I BEAT
HIS ASS OUT THERE.

13:12.478 --> 13:14.247
HE DIDN'T EVEN TURN
THE PHONES BACK ON.

13:14.247 --> 13:16.149
WHAT THE HELL MAKES YOU THINK
YOU'RE GONNA GET IT DONE?

13:16.149 --> 13:18.318
I DIDN'T SEE YOU
BEAT NOBODY'S ASS.

13:18.318 --> 13:19.553
DUDE, I BEAT HIS ASS.

13:19.553 --> 13:21.187
THAT OLD MAN
HELD HIS OWN, THOUGH.

13:21.187 --> 13:22.989
DAWG.
LOOK, MAN.

13:22.989 --> 13:24.357
I BEAT HIS ASS.

13:24.357 --> 13:25.859
ALL RIGHT, LOOK,
I'M GONNA CALL IT A DRAW.

13:25.859 --> 13:27.127
HELL, NO,
IT AIN'T NO DRAW.

13:27.127 --> 13:28.762
WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT PHONES, ALL RIGHT?

13:28.762 --> 13:30.096
AND I DID TALK TO HIM.

13:30.096 --> 13:32.165
AND, BENNY, SOMETIMES
A CONVERSATION'S ENOUGH,
ALL RIGHT?

13:32.165 --> 13:34.701
YEAH. I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE HELL YOU WERE WATCHING,

13:34.701 --> 13:36.036
BUT I BEAT HIS OLD ASS
OUT THERE.

13:36.036 --> 13:38.271
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

13:38.271 --> 13:39.506
GET IT, DUDE.

13:39.506 --> 13:40.707
BENNY'S TOWING.

13:40.707 --> 13:42.475
YEAH.

13:42.475 --> 13:44.077
YEAH, NO, WE JUST HAD
A SMALL PROBLEM WITH THE PHONES.

13:44.077 --> 13:45.879
ALL GOOD, THOUGH.
UH, WHAT'S THE ADDRESS?

13:45.879 --> 13:47.514
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

13:47.514 --> 13:49.583
YEAH, I GOT IT.
I GOT IT.

13:49.583 --> 13:52.553
OKAY.

13:52.553 --> 13:54.888
BENNY'S TOWING.
YO, IT'S SAM.

13:54.888 --> 13:56.723
COME ON, SAM. YOU KNOW
WE'RE STILL IN BUSINESS.

13:56.723 --> 13:58.391
NAH, MAN, WE JUST HAD
SOME PHONE PROBLEMS,

13:58.391 --> 14:00.126
BUT IT'S ALL GOOD
RIGHT NOW.

14:00.126 --> 14:01.835
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, RIGHT.

14:01.835 --> 14:03.637
OH, THEY'RE
ALL PARKED ILLEGALLY?

14:03.637 --> 14:05.606
OOH, CASH, BABY.
ALL RIGHT, WE'LL BE THERE.

14:05.606 --> 14:06.707
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:06.707 --> 14:08.408
BENNY'S TOWING.

14:08.408 --> 14:11.978
YEAH, ADDRESS, PLEASE.

14:11.978 --> 14:13.714
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA GET YOU
ON THE BOOKS RIGHT NOW.

14:13.714 --> 14:16.082
I GOT, UH,
MAYBE LIKE A HOUR, 45.

14:16.082 --> 14:17.250
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:17.250 --> 14:19.019
YEAH? OKAY.

14:19.019 --> 14:20.020
OKAY.

14:20.020 --> 14:22.122
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

14:22.122 --> 14:24.658
BENNY'S TOWING.
YEAH.

14:24.658 --> 14:26.392
YEAH, SURE, SURE.

14:26.392 --> 14:28.161
YEAH, ABOUT 50 MINUTES.

14:28.161 --> 14:29.930
ALL RIGHT.

14:29.930 --> 14:30.931
WHAT THE HELL?

14:30.931 --> 14:32.232
DAWG.
MITCH.

14:32.232 --> 14:33.967
GET OFF THAT ASS AND START
MAKING SOME MONEY, HUH?

14:33.967 --> 14:35.468
‐DAWG, WHAT'D YOU DO?
‐COME ON, BABY.

14:35.468 --> 14:36.503
I TOLD YOU
I TALKED TO HIM.

14:36.503 --> 14:37.938
NAH, YOU DID SOMETHING.
YEAH.

14:37.938 --> 14:39.472
NO, I DIDN'T DO NOTHING.
WHAT'D YOU DO?

14:39.472 --> 14:40.774
I JUST TALKED TO HIM,
THAT'S IT.

14:40.774 --> 14:42.676
HEY. WHAT'D YOU DO?
TALKED TO HIM, TALKED TO HIM.

14:42.676 --> 14:45.211
MUST HAVE BEEN THAT ASS
WHUPPING YOU GAVE HIM, HUH?

14:45.211 --> 14:47.948
AH! I TOLD YOU.
COME ON, BABY.

14:47.948 --> 14:49.249
I TOLD YOU.
I TOLD YOU.

14:49.249 --> 14:50.350
OH, HOLD ON.

14:50.350 --> 14:51.552
LET'S GO MAKE
SOME MONEY, HUH?

14:51.552 --> 14:53.119
YEAH.

15:01.602 --> 15:03.770
GIRL, IS THIS MAN
EVEN COMING?

15:03.770 --> 15:05.038
I DON'T KNOW.

15:05.038 --> 15:07.373
[ SIGHS ]
I NEED TO GO TO SLEEP.

15:07.373 --> 15:08.742
LET'S JUST GIVE IT
ANOTHER HOUR.

15:08.742 --> 15:10.043
I HAVE TO WORK
IN THE MORNING.

15:10.043 --> 15:12.979
I WILL PAY YOU
IF IT ALL WORKS OUT.

15:12.979 --> 15:15.015
GIRL, YOU ALREADY OWE ME
FOR THE LAST TIME I DID THIS.

15:15.015 --> 15:16.717
AREN'T YOU IN ACTING CLASS?

15:16.717 --> 15:17.818
YES.

15:17.818 --> 15:20.453
AND ISN'T THIS
GOOD PRACTICE?

15:20.453 --> 15:21.555
I GUESS.

15:21.555 --> 15:23.489
MM.
THANK YOU.

15:23.489 --> 15:25.458
SO THEN <i>YOU</i> SHOULD
BE PAYING <i>ME.</i>

15:25.458 --> 15:27.761
GIRL, YOU AND
MISS CANDACE GONNA KILL ME.

15:27.761 --> 15:29.663
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:33.900 --> 15:35.969
I THINK THAT'S HIM.

15:35.969 --> 15:37.971
OH, THAT'S HIM?

15:37.971 --> 15:39.272
YOU READY?

15:39.272 --> 15:40.541
YEAH.

15:40.541 --> 15:43.510
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

15:43.510 --> 15:44.945
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN.

15:44.945 --> 15:46.012
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T.

15:46.012 --> 15:47.280
LOOK, I DIDN'T KNOW
SHE WAS THERE.

15:47.280 --> 15:50.283
BUT YOU DID KNOW
YOU HAD A WIFE.

15:50.283 --> 15:51.952
HOW CAN
I MAKE THIS UP TO YOU?

15:51.952 --> 15:54.120
YOU LIED TO ME
ALL THIS TIME.

15:54.120 --> 15:57.558
I'LL HAVE A SCOTCH, NEAT.

15:57.558 --> 15:59.225
GO HOME TO YOUR WIFE.

15:59.225 --> 16:00.767
I AM SORRY.

16:00.767 --> 16:02.569
YEAH, I KNOW.

16:02.569 --> 16:04.104
[ SIGHS ]

16:04.104 --> 16:05.438
YOU KNOW
WE CAN'T SEE EACH OTHER.

16:05.438 --> 16:07.574
DON'T YOU DARE!

16:07.574 --> 16:09.109
YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT'S MARRIED.

16:09.109 --> 16:12.045
DON'T YOU DARE ACT AS THOUGH
YOU'RE ENDING THIS WITH ME.

16:12.045 --> 16:13.647
AND IF I HAD KNOWN
THAT YOU WERE MARRIED,

16:13.647 --> 16:16.282
I NEVER WOULD HAVE
LET YOU GET THIS FAR.

16:16.282 --> 16:18.051
GO. JUST GO.

16:18.051 --> 16:19.620
I LOVE YOU.

16:19.620 --> 16:21.254
[ Voice breaking ]
I NEVER WANT TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

16:21.254 --> 16:23.890
I REALLY DO LOVE YOU.
GO LOVE YOU WIFE!

16:25.892 --> 16:27.861
OKAY.

16:27.861 --> 16:30.330
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

16:30.330 --> 16:32.365
[ SNIFFLES ] BYE.

16:34.134 --> 16:35.802
[ CRYING ]

16:48.214 --> 16:50.150
PARDON ME. HERE.

16:50.150 --> 16:52.586
I DON'T NEED
YOUR DAMN NAPKIN!

16:53.520 --> 16:55.221
[ SOBBING ]

17:10.611 --> 17:12.312
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

17:14.014 --> 17:15.281
CANDACE: Hello?

17:15.281 --> 17:16.650
MOM?

17:19.553 --> 17:21.087
IT WORKED.

17:21.087 --> 17:23.023
What did I tell you?

17:23.023 --> 17:24.825
I JUST ‐‐ I WALKED AWAY.

17:24.825 --> 17:27.728
WERE YOU MEAN TO HIM?

17:27.728 --> 17:29.395
YEAH.

17:29.395 --> 17:31.264
GOOD GIRL.

17:31.264 --> 17:32.933
SHOULD I GO BACK?

17:32.933 --> 17:34.034
Not tonight.

17:34.034 --> 17:36.202
HE SCARES EASILY.

17:36.202 --> 17:38.438
GO BACK TOMORROW
AND APOLOGIZE.

17:38.438 --> 17:41.307
YOU DID ENOUGH FOR TODAY.

17:41.307 --> 17:42.576
THE SEED IS PLANTED.

17:42.576 --> 17:45.211
WELL...

17:45.211 --> 17:47.080
YOU HAD THIS MAN PEGGED.

17:47.080 --> 17:50.250
YEAH, LIKE MOST MEN,
EXCEPT FOR THIS ONE.

17:50.250 --> 17:51.585
WHERE ARE YOU?

17:51.585 --> 17:53.620
I drove to the house
in the suburbs.

17:53.620 --> 17:56.022
HE'S HAVING DINNER
WITH A FAMILY.

17:56.022 --> 17:57.724
LOOKS LIKE A WIFE AND KIDS.

17:57.724 --> 18:00.734
AND HE LIVES HERE LOCALLY.

18:00.734 --> 18:03.269
YOU SERIOUS?
Yeah.

18:03.269 --> 18:05.939
HE PASSED BY THIS HOUSE
FOUR TIMES,

18:05.939 --> 18:07.407
SO I KIND OF HAD A FEELING.

18:07.407 --> 18:11.712
SO I SAT HERE
AND WAITED FOR HIM.

18:11.712 --> 18:13.379
I WALKED TO THE MAILBOX.

18:13.379 --> 18:16.116
HIS NAME IS BRANDON MAVEN.

18:16.116 --> 18:19.419
HER NAME IS MARTHA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:19.419 --> 18:21.788
IT'S LIKE OUT OF A STORYBOOK.

18:21.788 --> 18:23.423
IS IT?

18:23.423 --> 18:24.958
Yeah.

18:26.159 --> 18:28.762
BUT I'M ABOUT
TO MAKE IT A NIGHTMARE.

18:30.130 --> 18:31.131
TONIGHT?

18:31.131 --> 18:32.633
NO.

18:32.633 --> 18:33.734
TIMING.

18:33.734 --> 18:35.602
Remember timing.

18:35.602 --> 18:37.804
[ Sighs ]
I'm gonna go home.

18:37.804 --> 18:39.239
I'LL CALL YOU TOMORROW.

18:39.239 --> 18:40.541
OKAY.

18:40.541 --> 18:42.743
Okay, bye.
BYE.

18:42.743 --> 18:44.745
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

18:51.051 --> 18:52.285
[ SIGHS ]

18:52.285 --> 18:54.821
GOOD NIGHT, BRANDON.

19:02.503 --> 19:05.271
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

19:19.085 --> 19:21.187
♪♪♪♪

19:39.305 --> 19:40.741
HI.

19:40.741 --> 19:43.276
[ GASPS ]
OH, YOU SCARED ME.

19:43.276 --> 19:45.411
OH, I'M SORRY.

19:45.411 --> 19:47.681
OH.
WELL, SHE'S NOT THERE.

19:47.681 --> 19:49.315
NO?
NO.

19:52.519 --> 19:53.954
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:53.954 --> 19:57.057
WALKING MY DOG.

19:57.057 --> 19:59.292
I DON'T SEE A DOG
ON THE LEASH.

19:59.292 --> 20:00.961
OH. [ LAUGHS ]
WELL...

20:00.961 --> 20:03.770
YOU KNOW, I USED TO WALK HER
BEFORE SHE DIED.

20:03.770 --> 20:07.508
AND THEN EVER SINCE THEN, I JUST
CARRY THE LEASH WHEN I WALK.

20:07.508 --> 20:09.109
IT'S GOOD EXERCISE,
YOU KNOW.

20:09.109 --> 20:12.212
YEAH.
YEAH.

20:12.212 --> 20:13.446
[ SNIFFING ]
OOH.

20:13.446 --> 20:16.717
DO YOU SMELL SOMETHING?
[ SNIFFING ]

20:16.717 --> 20:18.018
NO, MA'AM, I DON'T.

20:18.018 --> 20:20.887
OOH!
SOMETHING SMELLS FOUL.

20:20.887 --> 20:22.823
I'M GONNA CALL THE CITY
AND HAVE THEM COME OUT HERE

20:22.823 --> 20:23.990
AND CHECK THE SEWER.

20:23.990 --> 20:25.892
[ SNIFFING ]
OOH, THAT'S FOUL.

20:25.892 --> 20:27.127
OOH.

20:27.127 --> 20:29.495
OKAY.
DO YOU THINK IT'S GAS?

20:29.495 --> 20:32.332
DO YOU THINK
IT'S NATURAL GAS?

20:32.332 --> 20:33.700
NO, MA'AM.
I DON'T SMELL ANYTHING.

20:33.700 --> 20:35.869
OH, WELL, IF IT IS,
THAT'S DANGEROUS, YOU KNOW.

20:35.869 --> 20:37.137
YES.
WELL...

20:37.137 --> 20:39.940
[ SNIFFING ] OOH.

20:39.940 --> 20:42.375
WELL, SHE'S NOT HERE.
DO YOU HAVE A KEY?

20:42.375 --> 20:45.712
NO, MA'AM.

20:45.712 --> 20:47.581
WELL, ARE YOU
GONNA COME BACK LATER?

20:47.581 --> 20:50.817
NO. I THINK I'M GONNA
SIT HERE AND WAIT FOR HER.

20:52.919 --> 20:55.255
OH, WELL,
IT MUST BE IMPORTANT.

20:55.255 --> 20:58.892
YES, MA'AM, IT IS.

20:58.892 --> 21:03.770
YOU KNOW, I NEVER DID SEE
THAT MAN COME OUT OF THAT HOUSE.

21:03.770 --> 21:07.473
IS THAT RIGHT?
MM‐HMM.

21:07.473 --> 21:09.275
YOU SAID YOU HAD
A PICTURE OF HIM.

21:09.275 --> 21:10.911
OH, I DO.
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

21:10.911 --> 21:13.914
WELL, I DON'T USUALLY TRAVEL
AROUND WITH A PICTURE OF HIM,

21:13.914 --> 21:17.584
BUT I HAD IT BECAUSE
I WANTED TO CHECK SOMETHING.

21:17.584 --> 21:20.887
I WANTED TO LOOK
AT THIS DOOR AGAIN.

21:20.887 --> 21:24.324
YOU KNOW, MY HUSBAND
WAS A POLICE OFFICER.

21:24.324 --> 21:25.726
IS THAT SO?
OH, YES.

21:25.726 --> 21:27.861
AND MY SON'S
A POLICE OFFICER NOW, YES.

21:27.861 --> 21:31.131
AND MY SON‐IN‐LAW
IS THE CHIEF OF POLICE.

21:31.131 --> 21:33.433
OH, OKAY.
MM‐HMM.

21:33.433 --> 21:36.603
NOW, DO YOU KNOW HIM?

21:36.603 --> 21:40.106
YES.

21:40.106 --> 21:42.308
QUINCY.

21:42.308 --> 21:44.511
QUINCY MAXWELL.

21:44.511 --> 21:46.713
QUINCY MAXWELL.

21:46.713 --> 21:48.915
AND YOU SAW HIM
GO INTO THIS HOUSE?

21:48.915 --> 21:52.285
OH, YES, I DID.

21:52.285 --> 21:54.420
MY DAUGHTER LET HIM IN.

21:54.420 --> 21:57.390
WELL, I DIDN'T EXACTLY SEE HER
OPEN THE DOOR, YOU KNOW.

21:57.390 --> 21:58.625
BUT I DID SEE HIM GO IN.

21:58.625 --> 22:01.267
YEAH, AND RIGHT
AFTER HE WENT IN,

22:01.267 --> 22:03.436
A WHITE MAN RAN OUT ‐‐
RIGHT IMMEDIATELY.

22:03.436 --> 22:05.005
AND HE WAS
VERY WELL‐DRESSED.

22:05.005 --> 22:07.608
AND I FIGURED
THAT THIS MAN CAUGHT THEM

22:07.608 --> 22:10.577
IN SOME KIND OF
A COMPROMISING SITUATION.

22:13.313 --> 22:15.782
BUT YOU'RE SURE YOU SAW HIM
GO INTO THIS HOUSE?

22:15.782 --> 22:17.584
OF COURSE I ‐‐
WELL, IT'S ON CAMERA.

22:17.584 --> 22:18.619
I'M NOT CRAZY.

22:18.619 --> 22:19.820
OH, MA'AM,
I DIDN'T SAY YOU WERE.

22:19.820 --> 22:22.155
OH, YOU'RE JUST
LIKE MY CHILDREN.

22:22.155 --> 22:25.091
IF I FORGET ONE LITTLE THING,
THEY THINK I HAVE ALZHEIMER'S.

22:25.091 --> 22:26.627
WELL,
IF IT'S ON THE CAMERA,

22:26.627 --> 22:28.695
THE CAMERA DOES NOT
HAVE DEMENTIA.

22:28.695 --> 22:30.597
NO, MA'AM, I KNOW.
MM.

22:30.597 --> 22:32.599
NO, I SAW HIM GO IN.

22:37.103 --> 22:39.472
OH.
I HAVE TO GO.

22:54.555 --> 22:57.023
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

22:57.023 --> 22:59.526
CANDACE, WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO
TO LET YOU GIVE ME THAT BABY?

22:59.526 --> 23:00.694
[ SCOFFS ]

23:00.694 --> 23:02.268
THERE IS NOTHING
YOU CAN GIVE ME,

23:02.268 --> 23:04.470
NOT A DAMN THING.

23:04.470 --> 23:07.140
WHAT DO YOU HAVE, HUH?

23:07.140 --> 23:09.610
I KNOW
YOU'RE AFRAID OF QUINCY.

23:09.610 --> 23:14.347
THAT WOMAN SHOWED ME A PICTURE
OF HIM WALKING IN THIS HOUSE.

23:14.347 --> 23:15.348
SHE SHOWED YOU THAT?

23:15.348 --> 23:16.617
YES!

23:16.617 --> 23:19.052
GIVE HIM TO ME!

23:19.052 --> 23:22.523
DON'T LET HIM
GO INTO THE SYSTEM.

23:22.523 --> 23:23.757
I NEED YOU TO LEAVE.

23:23.757 --> 23:25.258
WHAT DO YOU NEED ME TO DO?

23:25.258 --> 23:27.027
BEG AGAIN SOME MORE?

23:27.027 --> 23:29.630
WHAT?
GO HOME, HANNA.

23:32.232 --> 23:34.801
WHEREVER THAT IS.

23:34.801 --> 23:36.069
CANDACE, IF HAD THE MONEY,

23:36.069 --> 23:39.906
I KNOW THAT WOULD MAKE YOU
GIVE HIM TO ME.

23:39.906 --> 23:42.576
WELL, YOU HAVE
TO HAVE SOMETHING.

23:42.576 --> 23:45.145
I DON'T HAVE NOTHING.

23:45.145 --> 23:46.212
NO.

23:47.814 --> 23:50.751
I GOT...

23:50.751 --> 23:55.856
I GOT $867 TO MY NAME.

23:55.856 --> 23:59.159
YOU WANT THAT?

23:59.159 --> 24:02.903
HMM?

24:02.903 --> 24:05.371
GIVE IT TO ME.

24:05.371 --> 24:07.708
HERE. HERE.

24:12.312 --> 24:13.714
[ MONEY RUSTLING ]

24:13.714 --> 24:15.448
HM.

24:18.919 --> 24:21.121
THIS WON'T EVEN
BUY ME A PURSE.

24:24.024 --> 24:26.560
NOW WILL YOU CALL?

24:33.233 --> 24:35.769
I WANT MORE.

24:38.104 --> 24:39.339
CANDACE.

24:42.208 --> 24:44.745
TAKE YOUR LITTLE MONEY.

24:50.717 --> 24:53.820
YOU HAVE NOTHING.

24:53.820 --> 24:57.591
NOTHING.

24:57.591 --> 24:59.926
NOTHING TO OFFER ME.

25:02.503 --> 25:04.070
OKAY.

25:08.842 --> 25:12.613
PLEASE.

25:12.613 --> 25:14.380
GET OFF MY PROPERTY, HANNA.

25:16.850 --> 25:19.185
OH, AND DON'T WALK
ON MY DAMN GRASS.

25:23.590 --> 25:24.658
WAIT.

25:27.594 --> 25:30.263
THERE IS SOMETHING
THAT YOU CAN DO.

25:32.498 --> 25:35.035
ANYTHING.

25:37.604 --> 25:40.006
TELL BENNY
TO SUE THE CRYERS.

25:42.175 --> 25:45.078
CANDACE,
WHAT IS THAT TO YOU?

25:45.078 --> 25:47.614
WHAT IS IT TO <i>YOU?</i>

25:50.450 --> 25:53.554
TELL HIM TO SUE...

25:53.554 --> 25:56.790
AND I'LL BRING YOU MY SON.

25:56.790 --> 26:00.493
CANDACE, WHY WOULD YOU ‐‐
WYATT HIT HIM.

26:00.493 --> 26:03.036
HE SHOULD PAY.

26:03.036 --> 26:04.571
YOU GOT THAT MONEY
FROM THAT MAN.

26:04.571 --> 26:08.842
THAT'S MY MONEY, OKAY?

26:08.842 --> 26:11.277
THAT BOY HIT MY BROTHER.

26:11.277 --> 26:13.947
HE SHOULD PAY,
AND YOU SHOULD LET HIM SUE.

26:13.947 --> 26:16.449
YOUR MONEY?

26:16.449 --> 26:17.851
YOUR MONEY?

26:17.851 --> 26:21.087
YOU BLACKMAILED THAT MAN.

26:21.087 --> 26:23.156
BENNY SHOULD HAVE
HIS OWN MONEY.

26:23.156 --> 26:25.025
YOU TOOK THAT MONEY
FROM THAT MAN.

26:25.025 --> 26:26.993
THEY DON'T OWE BENNY NOTHING.

26:28.962 --> 26:32.198
SO, IF I DIDN'T BUY
THAT TOW YARD FOR BENNY,

26:32.198 --> 26:34.768
WOULD YOU LET HIM SUE THEN?
THAT WOULD BE HIS CALL.

26:34.768 --> 26:36.202
THAT DOESN'T MAKE
ANY DAMN SENSE TO ME.

26:36.202 --> 26:37.638
WHY NOT?

26:37.638 --> 26:40.641
I'M NOT BENNY.
I'M NOT DOING THAT.

26:40.641 --> 26:43.109
AND I'M NOT BRINGING YOU
MY SON.

26:43.109 --> 26:46.012
HOW ABOUT THAT?

26:46.012 --> 26:49.683
SO YOU'LL BLACKMAIL ME ‐‐

26:49.683 --> 26:52.819
YOUR MOTHER...

26:52.819 --> 26:54.755
WITH YOUR OWN CHILD?

26:58.659 --> 27:01.034
IT'S NOT BLACKMAIL.

27:01.034 --> 27:02.969
WHO ARE YOU, GIRL?

27:06.940 --> 27:10.276
OKAY.

27:10.276 --> 27:13.747
OKAY.

27:13.747 --> 27:15.916
I'M DONE. [ SCOFFS ]

27:15.916 --> 27:18.852
YOU PROMISE?

27:18.852 --> 27:22.022
'CAUSE YOU'VE SAID THAT
BEFORE.

27:22.022 --> 27:24.224
I KNOW.

27:24.224 --> 27:25.659
I KNOW.

27:29.429 --> 27:33.133
AND HERE YOU ARE
ONCE AGAIN.

27:37.838 --> 27:40.173
NUMBER ONE ‐‐

27:40.173 --> 27:41.742
'CAUSE YOU'LL
NEVER UNDERSTAND

27:41.742 --> 27:44.511
WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE A MOTHER

27:44.511 --> 27:46.913
WHO HAS HOPE FOR HER CHILD.

27:49.983 --> 27:54.420
AND NUMBER TWO ‐‐
'CAUSE HE'S SO PRECIOUS...

27:57.057 --> 27:58.925
...AND SO INNOCENT.

28:01.535 --> 28:04.070
AND YOU...

28:13.079 --> 28:15.616
GOODBYE, HANNA.

28:23.624 --> 28:25.325
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

28:43.710 --> 28:45.812
♪♪♪♪

28:45.812 --> 28:47.447
HI.
HI.

28:47.447 --> 28:48.549
MARTY GOT YOU IN HERE?

28:48.549 --> 28:51.384
YEP.
IT'S ALL DONE.

28:51.384 --> 28:52.953
GOOD.

28:52.953 --> 28:55.221
SHE SIGNED EVERYTHING.

28:55.221 --> 28:56.557
GREAT.

28:56.557 --> 28:59.626
OF COURSE, SHE MADE ME
GIVE IT ALL TO HER IN CASH.

28:59.626 --> 29:00.634
REALLY?

29:00.634 --> 29:03.570
YEAH.

29:03.570 --> 29:04.671
HUH.

29:04.671 --> 29:06.807
I HAD TO GO
TO ALL THE BRANCHES

29:06.807 --> 29:08.441
TO GET IT TOGETHER.

29:08.441 --> 29:09.776
BUT YOU DID IT?

29:09.776 --> 29:11.612
